  					<td align=center valign="top" width=100%><br>
  						<!--#beginContent#-->
  						<table align='center' cellpadding=5 width='85%'>  <tr><td class='spti2' width='100%'>PLAYER STRATEGY - SHAMAN</td></tr>  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><font class='dbti'>BARBARIAN SHAMAN 1 TO 9; A STRATEGIE</font> - <small>Scepter, Luclin</td></tr>
  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><p>Hail,<br>
<Br>
I am currently a 9th level Shaman, and I will try to give some advice on how you can possibly play a barbarian from level 1 to 8 (and do it fast). 
First things first. When creating the character I used this website for dividing my 30 statpoints, and I am very glad I did so. My barbarian has been very balanced in his skills so far. <Br>
Second, I have used only 2 training points so far. I am not one to do this so I can pump them al in one skill somewhere around level 30, but what I noticed was that the barbarian shaman is such a strong character (I will get back to that) he does not need the skillpoints (so far). The only 2 points I used so far were to learn the basics of channeling (level 4) and meditate (level 8). <Br>
When you first start out, learn your spells (minor healing and inner fire). Buff yourself and head out to your guild. I advise you at least talk to  at your guild and  at the warrior guild. These persons will give you bags for quests which you can use for your own personel use. Now you can head out to the everfrost newbie area. Oh, when crossing the lake in front of Halas, swim everytime. It will get your swimming skill up pretty easy.<br>
Ok, let the fun begin. The everfrost newbie hunting area is such a fun one. It is like shooting ducks at the shootingstand. All the creatures will be passing the entrance to Halas zone. White wolfs, Polar Bear Cubs, Wooly Spiderlings, Ice Goblins, Gnoll Pups and Decaying Skels. They practically all agro on u at this point, with exception of the spiderling, but they will band together. The goblins, gnolls and skels are level 1, the polar’s and wolfs are level 2, and the wooly’s are level 1 to 3 (be sure to con them). <br>
I advice you to try to take out all decaying skells, especially the ones with cracked staffs. Keep the bone chips to sell as stacks to necros for 3pp each. (Watch out for vengefull skels which also roam this part of the zone, not very nice bonies.) First make enough money to get your first level spells. Especially Burst of Flame which is great for pulling at this stage. You don’t have to use your attack spells during fights, if you are fully buffed you can probably take out the white wolfs and polar cub’s by tanking them. You are gonna be level 2 pretty fast. <br>
If you have your spells save up for a large sewing kitt. It is an investment which is gonna keep you armored at least until level 9. You can use all ruined bear pelts to make your own armor. The vendor is conveniently located at the Halas zone. You can get most patterns there also. All spiderling silk you can use for making silk thread, which can be used for silk bandages. You probably dont need these, but it is good for training your skill. <br>
For me this meant hanging around everfrost newbie area until I was level 4. Then I went to Qeynos Hills. I would advice you to wait until level 5. You can get the spell gate then, so the trip back is easy. Ask for an escort for travelling through blackburrow if you are not familiar with the terrain. All gnolls except the pups will agro. If you do wait until level 5 you can get your spells and move to qeynos hills and stay there until level 8. You only have to go back once, and preferably as soon as you can. Finish the initiate quest. You first had to talk to Jinkus at the guild for that. It will provide you with a very nice magic summonable weapon. <br>
Qeynos Hills is gonna be a perfect area for you. Take on the large and giant bats. If the con even you can tank them (assuming you were your buffs), taking on yellows is no problem either, but you have to use sicken (and I would advise drowsy). Take out all rabid wolfs (watch out for Holly), and have some fun with the Gnolls outside blackburrow. You will be eight in no time if you do this. <Br>
Gate back and learn meditate. <br>
My personel experience with level 8 wasn’t as good as the other levels. But I was taking out my first wisps and rabid grizzlys. Just sicken, drowsy and nuke them. Great experience, but quit a manadrain, so after that I took out the stronger Giant bats. I hope you have saved up some money by now, because level 9 is coming up, and you are definitly going to need your new DoT and off course SoW. <br>
Take out more wisps and rabid grizzlys. I do not enjoy bb yet because to many Gnolls still agro. I am gonna go there when that stops and I can take out Guardsmen without being trained. And the Greater Lightstone quest is gonna enable me to get good money.<br>
That was what I had to say about the first levels of being a Shaman. What I esspecially wanted to make clear is that until you reach 9 you are gonna be able to tank most even’s and in combination with DoT’s and nukes you can still take out yellow’s.<Br>
Good hunting,<Br></p>

		</td></tr>
